{
    "Description": "<h3>Usage</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">component.live()\n</pre><ul><li>Returns a boolean indicating whether the component is currently<strong> </strong>running live<strong> </strong>as part of an active interface (as opposed to running inside the editor or test mode).</li></ul><h3><br></h3><h3>Notes</h3><ul><li>Use this function to differentiate behavior between development and production:</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">In the editor or when running manually, <code>component.live()</code> returns <code>false</code>.</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">When the component is part of a live running interface, it returns <code>true</code>.</li><li>This is especially useful for:</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">Skipping production-only operations (e.g., sending messages, writing to external systems) during development.</li><li class=\"ql-indent-1\">Adding debug logging or test data paths when working inside the editor.</li></ul><h3><br></h3><h3>Returns</h3><ul><li><code>true</code> if the component is running live, <code>false</code> otherwise. <em><u>(bool)</u></em></li></ul><p><br></p><h3>Example</h3><pre class=\"ql-syntax\" spellcheck=\"false\">if component.live() then\n&nbsp; &nbsp; -- Production behavior: process real data\n&nbsp; &nbsp; trace(\"Component is running live\")\nelse\n&nbsp; &nbsp; -- Development behavior: run test or debug code\n&nbsp; &nbsp; trace(\"Component is running in editor/test mode\")\nend\n</pre>",
    "Name": "component.live",
    "Parameters": null,
    "ParameterTable": false,
    "SummaryLine": "Returns true if the component is running in live (production) mode."
}